<paragraph id="8B9B36C86369FFC3FF67EE9F4AB4F832" blockId="5.[151,1437,1651,2038]" pageId="5" pageNumber="124">
<emphasis id="B950EADA6369FFC3FF67EE9F4A7DF912" bold="true" box="[199,269,1723,1749]" pageId="5" pageNumber="124">Male:</emphasis>
Body length 5.5–6.0 mm, forewing length 6.0– 
<quantity id="4CDC9B2D6369FFC3FCE1EE9F48ECF911" box="[833,924,1723,1750]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.5" pageId="5" pageNumber="124" unit="mm" value="6.5">6.5 mm</quantity>
, hindwing length 5.5–6.0 mm (n = 5). Medium-sized 
<taxonomicName id="4C244D4B6369FFC3FEBCEEFB4AEDF93E" authorityName="Navas" authorityYear="1934" box="[284,413,1759,1785]" class="Insecta" family="Chloroperlidae" genus="Haploperla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="124" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B950EADA6369FFC3FEBCEEFB4AEDF93E" box="[284,413,1759,1785]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="124">Haploperla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Triocellate, Body color is pale yellow; head yellowish and intraocellar area light brown; compound eyes dark black. Pronotum yellow, posteriorly and anteriorly with a brown stripe on a disc (
<figureCitation id="131F2A4D6369FFC3FA94EF274EFFF8D9" box="[1332,1423,1795,1822]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1522,1546]" captionTargetBox="[153,1435,181,1498]" captionTargetId="figure-31@6.[153,1435,181,1499]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 6. Haploperla tuanjiena Du &amp; Chen, 2016. Male, A: head and pronotum; B: terminalia dorsal; C: epiproct dorsal; D: terminalia ventral." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6479628" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6479628/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="124">Fig. 6A</figureCitation>
). Tergum 9 posterior margins were slightly plump and covered with hairs. Tergum 10 divided, median portion forming a triangular structure to the base of epiproct. Epiproct subtriangular in dorsal view, inflated in lateral view, and anterolateral margin strongly sclerotized; posterodorsal area membranous; apex of epiproct sharp (
<figureCitation id="131F2A4D6369FFC3FAB1EF4B4EE0F84D" box="[1297,1424,1903,1930]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1522,1546]" captionTargetBox="[153,1435,181,1498]" captionTargetId="figure-31@6.[153,1435,181,1499]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 6. Haploperla tuanjiena Du &amp; Chen, 2016. Male, A: head and pronotum; B: terminalia dorsal; C: epiproct dorsal; D: terminalia ventral." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6479628" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6479628/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="124">Fig. 6B–D</figureCitation>
). Aedeagus enlarged, membranous rounded, dorsally covered with scattered small spines, ventrolaterally with a pair of sclerotized stylus and with a patch of sclerotized spines, the patch of spines in ventral view look like ear-shape on both sides (
<figureCitation id="131F2A4D6369FFC3FE9AEFFF4AC7F832" box="[314,439,2011,2037]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="7.[131,230,1527,1551]" captionTargetBox="[136,1410,267,1504]" captionTargetId="figure-84@7.[136,1410,267,1504]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 7. Haploperla tuanjiena Du &amp; Chen, 2016. Male, A: aedeagus dorsal; B: aedeagus ventrolateral; C: aedeagus ventral; D: aedeagus lateral." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6479630" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6479630/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="124">Fig. 7A–D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF5B6640636AFFC0FF37EDD64A22F9E9" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6479628" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6479628" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6479628/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="125" startId="6.[151,250,1522,1546]" targetBox="[153,1435,181,1498]" targetPageId="6">
<paragraph id="8B9B36C8636AFFC0FF37EDD64A22F9E9" blockId="6.[151,1437,1522,1582]" pageId="6" pageNumber="125">
<emphasis id="B950EADA636AFFC0FF37EDD64A62F9CD" bold="true" box="[151,274,1522,1546]" pageId="6" pageNumber="125">FIGURE 6.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C244D4B636AFFC0FEB9EDD649DFF9CD" authority="Du &amp; Chen, 2016" authorityName="Du &amp; Chen" authorityYear="2016" box="[281,687,1522,1546]" class="Insecta" family="Chloroperlidae" genus="Haploperla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="125" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tuanjiena">
<emphasis id="B950EADA636AFFC0FEB9EDD64A83F9CD" box="[281,499,1522,1546]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="125">Haploperla tuanjiena</emphasis>
Du &amp; Chen, 2016
</taxonomicName>
. Male, A: head and pronotum; B: terminalia dorsal; C: epiproct dorsal; D: terminalia ventral.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8B9B36C8636AFFC0FF67EE794EE4F978" blockId="6.[151,1437,1628,2015]" pageId="6" pageNumber="125">
<emphasis id="B950EADA636AFFC0FF67EE794A58F9B0" bold="true" box="[199,296,1629,1655]" pageId="6" pageNumber="125">Female:</emphasis>
Body length 7.0 mm, forewing length 
<quantity id="4CDC9B2D636AFFC0FD78EE78485FF9B0" box="[728,815,1628,1655]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.5" pageId="6" pageNumber="125" unit="mm" value="7.5">7.5 mm</quantity>
, hindwing length 6.0 mm (n = 1). Head, pronotum disk, body color and pattern similar to males (
<figureCitation id="131F2A4D636AFFC0FDF9EEA449C3F95C" box="[601,691,1664,1691]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="8.[151,250,618,642]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,177,590]" captionTargetId="figure-165@8.[151,1435,177,590]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 8. Haploperla tuanjiena Du &amp; Chen, 2016. Female, A: head and pronotum; B: terminalia dorsal; C: terminalia ventral; D: subgenital plate." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6479632" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6479632/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="125">Fig. 8A</figureCitation>
). Terga 1–8 dorsally with large oval, brownish spots medially (
<figureCitation id="131F2A4D636AFFC0FACFEEA44BCBF978" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="8.[151,250,618,642]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,177,590]" captionTargetId="figure-165@8.[151,1435,177,590]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 8. Haploperla tuanjiena Du &amp; Chen, 2016. Female, A: head and pronotum; B: terminalia dorsal; C: terminalia ventral; D: subgenital plate." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6479632" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6479632/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="125">Fig. 8B</figureCitation>
). The small subgenital plate originating from tergum 8, the posterior margins are bluntly rounded (
<figureCitation id="131F2A4D636AFFC0FAADEE804EF8F978" box="[1293,1416,1700,1727]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="8.[151,250,618,642]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,177,590]" captionTargetId="figure-165@8.[151,1435,177,590]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 8. Haploperla tuanjiena Du &amp; Chen, 2016. Female, A: head and pronotum; B: terminalia dorsal; C: terminalia ventral; D: subgenital plate." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6479632" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6479632/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="125">Fig. 8C–D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C33E6543636AFFC1FF67EEED4E7FFF34" lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="126" pageId="6" pageNumber="125" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B9B36C8636AFFC1FF67EEED4E7FFF34" blockId="6.[151,1437,1628,2015]" lastBlockId="7.[131,1416,145,244]" lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="126" pageId="6" pageNumber="125">
<emphasis id="B950EADA636AFFC0FF67EEED4A4DF924" bold="true" box="[199,317,1737,1763]" pageId="6" pageNumber="125">Remarks:</emphasis>
According to 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB54B39636AFFC0FE7BEEEC49CCF924" author="Chen, Z. T. &amp; Du, Y." box="[475,700,1736,1763]" pageId="6" pageNumber="125" pagination="415 - 422" refId="ref3409" refString="Chen, Z. T. &amp; Du, Y. Z (2016 b) Two new species of Haploperla (Plecoptera: Chloroperlidae) from China. Zootaxa, 4196 (3), 415 - 422. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4196.3.5" type="journal article" year="2016">Chen &amp; Du (2016b)</bibRefCitation>
, this species is closely related to 
<taxonomicName id="4C244D4B636AFFC0FB89EEED4A66F8C0" authority="Zhiltzova &amp; Levanidova, 1978" authorityName="Zhiltzova &amp; Levanidova" authorityYear="1978" class="Insecta" family="Chloroperlidae" genus="Haploperla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="125" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="maritima">
<emphasis id="B950EADA636AFFC0FB89EEED4FC2F925" box="[1065,1202,1737,1762]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="125">H. maritima</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFB54B39636AFFC0FB18EEEC4A66F8C0" author="Zhiltzova, L. A. &amp; Levanidova, I. M." pageId="6" pageNumber="125" pagination="3 - 29" refId="ref4450" refString="Zhiltzova, L. A. &amp; Levanidova, I. M. (1978) New species of stoneflies (Plecoptera) from the Far East. Trudy Zoologicheskogo Instituta Akademii Nauk SSSR (Leningrad), 71, 3 - 29." type="journal article" year="1978">Zhiltzova &amp; Levanidova, 1978</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, known from the Russian Far East and 
<taxonomicName id="4C244D4B636AFFC0FD64EEC94886F8C0" authority="Zwick, 1977" authorityName="Zwick" authorityYear="1977" box="[708,1014,1772,1799]" class="Insecta" family="Chloroperlidae" genus="Haploperla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="125" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longicauda">
<emphasis id="B950EADA636AFFC0FD64EEC94813F8C1" box="[708,867,1772,1798]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="125">H. longicauda</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFB54B39636AFFC0FCC9EEC84886F8C0" author="Zwick, P." box="[873,1014,1772,1799]" pageId="6" pageNumber="125" pagination="85 - 134" refId="ref4531" refString="Zwick, P. (1977) Ergebnisse der Bhutan-Expedition 1972 des Naturhistorischen Museums in Basel. Plecoptera. Entomologica Basiliensia, 2, 85 - 134." type="journal article" year="1977">Zwick, 1977</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry id="F3337658636AFFC0FB98EEC84FFDF8C1" box="[1080,1165,1772,1798]" name="Bhutan" pageId="6" pageNumber="125">Bhutan</collectingCountry>
. Herein, we add that this species is also close to 
<taxonomicName id="4C244D4B636AFFC0FE36EF3549D6F8EC" authority="Li &amp; Yao, 2013" authorityName="Li &amp; Yao" authorityYear="2013" box="[406,678,1808,1835]" class="Insecta" family="Chloroperlidae" genus="Haploperla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="125" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="choui">
<emphasis id="B950EADA636AFFC0FE36EF354A85F8ED" box="[406,501,1808,1834]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="125">H. choui</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFB54B39636AFFC0FE5CEF3449D6F8EC" author="Li, W. H. &amp; Yao, G. &amp; Qin, X. F." box="[508,678,1808,1835]" pageId="6" pageNumber="125" pagination="550 - 556" refId="ref3752" refString="Li, W. H., Yao, G. &amp; Qin, X. F. (2013) Haploperla choui sp. n. (Plecoptera: Chloroperlidae), a remarkable new stonefly from Qinling Mountains of China. Zootaxa, 3640 (4), 550 - 556. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3640.4.3" type="journal article" year="2013">Li &amp; Yao, 2013</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
reported from Shaanxi, Qinling Mountains. The head and pronotum of 
<taxonomicName id="4C244D4B636AFFC0FF14EF114A63F889" authorityName="Li &amp; Yao" authorityYear="2013" box="[180,275,1844,1870]" class="Insecta" family="Chloroperlidae" genus="Haploperla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="125" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="choui">
<emphasis id="B950EADA636AFFC0FF14EF114A63F889" box="[180,275,1844,1870]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="125">H. choui</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are darkly pigmented (see 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB54B39636AFFC0FD9DEF1049A4F888" author="Li, W. H. &amp; Yao, G. &amp; Qin, X. F." box="[573,724,1844,1871]" pageId="6" pageNumber="125" pagination="550 - 556" refId="ref3752" refString="Li, W. H., Yao, G. &amp; Qin, X. F. (2013) Haploperla choui sp. n. (Plecoptera: Chloroperlidae), a remarkable new stonefly from Qinling Mountains of China. Zootaxa, 3640 (4), 550 - 556. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3640.4.3" type="journal article" year="2013">
Li 
<emphasis id="B950EADA636AFFC0FDFCEF1149E3F889" box="[604,659,1844,1870]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="125">et al.</emphasis>
2013
</bibRefCitation>
: figs. 3, 4), which is different from 
<taxonomicName id="4C244D4B636AFFC0FBF8EF114F93F889" authorityName="Du &amp; Chen" authorityYear="2016" box="[1112,1251,1845,1870]" class="Insecta" family="Chloroperlidae" genus="Haploperla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="125" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tuanjiena">
<emphasis id="B950EADA636AFFC0FBF8EF114F93F889" box="[1112,1251,1845,1870]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="125">H. tuanjiena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but the epiproct and aedeagus are close to 
<taxonomicName id="4C244D4B636AFFC0FE1DEF7D4939F8B5" authorityName="Du &amp; Chen" authorityYear="2016" box="[445,585,1881,1906]" class="Insecta" family="Chloroperlidae" genus="Haploperla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="125" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tuanjiena">
<emphasis id="B950EADA636AFFC0FE1DEF7D4939F8B5" box="[445,585,1881,1906]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="125">H. tuanjiena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The aedeagus of 
<taxonomicName id="4C244D4B636AFFC0FCB7EF7D4807F8B5" authorityName="Li &amp; Yao" authorityYear="2013" box="[791,887,1880,1906]" class="Insecta" family="Chloroperlidae" genus="Haploperla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="125" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="choui">
<emphasis id="B950EADA636AFFC0FCB7EF7D4807F8B5" box="[791,887,1880,1906]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="125">H. choui</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is also with a pair of stylus ventrolaterally, but a band of dense setae is present in the dorsal aspect. This band of dense setae is not present in 
<taxonomicName id="4C244D4B636AFFC0FB03EF594E40F851" authorityName="Du &amp; Chen" authorityYear="2016" box="[1187,1328,1917,1942]" class="Insecta" family="Chloroperlidae" genus="Haploperla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="125" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tuanjiena">
<emphasis id="B950EADA636AFFC0FB03EF594E40F851" box="[1187,1328,1917,1942]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="125">H. tuanjiena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; the head and pronotum are also not darkly pigmented (
<figureCitation id="131F2A4D636AFFC0FD3BEF844852F87D" box="[667,802,1952,1978]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1522,1546]" captionTargetBox="[153,1435,181,1498]" captionTargetId="figure-31@6.[153,1435,181,1499]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 6. Haploperla tuanjiena Du &amp; Chen, 2016. Male, A: head and pronotum; B: terminalia dorsal; C: epiproct dorsal; D: terminalia ventral." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6479628" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6479628/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="125">Figs. 6A–D</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="131F2A4D636AFFC0FC8EEF854806F87C" box="[814,886,1953,1979]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="7.[131,230,1527,1551]" captionTargetBox="[136,1410,267,1504]" captionTargetId="figure-84@7.[136,1410,267,1504]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 7. Haploperla tuanjiena Du &amp; Chen, 2016. Male, A: aedeagus dorsal; B: aedeagus ventrolateral; C: aedeagus ventral; D: aedeagus lateral." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6479630" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6479630/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="125">7A–D</figureCitation>
), which easily differentiates these species. In the original description of 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB54B39636AFFC0FE3AEFE049F0F818" author="Chen, Z. T. &amp; Du, Y." box="[410,640,1988,2015]" pageId="6" pageNumber="125" pagination="415 - 422" refId="ref3409" refString="Chen, Z. T. &amp; Du, Y. Z (2016 b) Two new species of Haploperla (Plecoptera: Chloroperlidae) from China. Zootaxa, 4196 (3), 415 - 422. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4196.3.5" type="journal article" year="2016">Chen &amp; Du (2016b)</bibRefCitation>
, the plates are not obvious, especially with regards to the epiproct and which may lead to misidentification in the future. The dorsal scattered spines on aedeagus and obvious lateral scales are absent (see 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB54B39636BFFC1FE91E891497DFF08" author="Chen, Z. T. &amp; Du, Y." box="[305,525,181,208]" pageId="7" pageNumber="126" pagination="415 - 422" refId="ref3409" refString="Chen, Z. T. &amp; Du, Y. Z (2016 b) Two new species of Haploperla (Plecoptera: Chloroperlidae) from China. Zootaxa, 4196 (3), 415 - 422. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4196.3.5" type="journal article" year="2016">Chen &amp; Du, 2016b</bibRefCitation>
: figs. 4–6). Therefore, we redescribed and gave good quality plates of epiproct and aedeagus with complete morphological characters and descriptions to avoid confusion in the future.
</paragraph>
